<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>Debugging on Voice of the Void</title><link>https://serenevoid.github.io/tags/debugging/</link><description>Recent content in Debugging on Voice of the Void</description><image><url>https://serenevoid.github.io/cover.gif</url><link>https://serenevoid.github.io/cover.gif</link></image><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><lastBuildDate>Thu, 08 Dec 2022 09:07:11 +0530</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://serenevoid.github.io/tags/debugging/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Still using console.log() for logging in JS? You can do better.</title><link>https://serenevoid.github.io/post/js_console/</link><pubDate>Thu, 08 Dec 2022 09:07:11 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://serenevoid.github.io/post/js_console/</guid><description>A simple guide to the console object and its methods in JS.</description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img loading="lazy" src="https://fireship.io/courses/javascript/img/console-hello-world.png" alt="console"  />

Probably the first thing every JS developer learns is the console.log() method.
Even the first Hello world program is written using this method in most
tutorials. But isn&rsquo;t it strange that most of us never dug deep into the console
object or it&rsquo;s other methods.</p>
<p>So I will take you through the console object and its methods in this blog.</p>
<h2 id="console">Console</h2>
<p>The <code>console</code> object gives you access to the browser&rsquo;s debugging console. It can
be accessed from any global object.</p>
<h2 id="instance-methods-of-console">Instance methods of console</h2>
<h3 id="consolelog">console.log()</h3>
<p>General logging of data into the console. Support multiple parameters and string
substitutions.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;Hello there&#34;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">&#34;Void&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>The output will look like this:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-console" data-lang="console"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">Hello there Void
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="consolewarn">console.warn()</h3>
<p>Outputs warning messages. Very similar to <code>console.log()</code>.
Supports additional arguments and also supports string substitutions.</p>
<h3 id="consoleerror">console.error()</h3>
<p>Outputs an error message. Can be used with string substitutions and additional
arguments just like <code>console.log()</code>.</p>
<h3 id="consoleclear">console.clear()</h3>
<p>Clears the console.</p>
<h3 id="consoleassert">console.assert()</h3>
<p>Log a message and stack trace to console if the first argument is <code>false</code>.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="kd">function</span> <span class="nx">min</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">a</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nx">b</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">a</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nx">b</span><span class="p">)</span> 
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nx">b</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="k">else</span> 
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nx">a</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="c1">// Test the function
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="c1"></span><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">result</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">min</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">assert</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">result</span> <span class="o">===</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Expected 2. Received 3&#39;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>The output will look like this:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-console" data-lang="console"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">Assertion failed: Expected 2. Received 3
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="consolecount">console.count()</h3>
<p>Logs the number of times this particular function has been called. It normally
stores the count under <code>default</code> key. But if we pass a string as an input, the
string will be used as the key for the counter. This can be used to set up
separate counters for bigger scripts.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="kd">function</span> <span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">key</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">key</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="c1">// Test the function
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="c1"></span><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;void&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;loop&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;void&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;loop&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;void&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">count</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;stage&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>The output will look like this:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-console" data-lang="console"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">void: 1
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">loop: 1
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">void: 2
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">loop: 2
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">void: 3
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">stage: 1
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="consolecountreset">console.countReset()</h3>
<p>Resets the counter value of the given key or <code>default</code> key.</p>
<h3 id="consolegroup">console.group()</h3>
<p>Create an <em>inline</em> group and indents all the next logs inside this group till
<code>console.groupEnd()</code> is called.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;Test&#34;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">// Start Test group
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="c1"></span><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;Hello&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;Void&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;Its a good day&#34;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">groupEnd</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&#34;Test&#34;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">// End Test group
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="consoletable">console.table()</h3>
<p>Displays tabular content in table form inside the console.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">table</span><span class="p">({</span><span class="s2">&#34;1&#34;</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="s2">&#34;2&#34;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">&#34;2&#34;</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="s2">&#34;sample text&#34;</span><span class="p">})</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>The output will look like a proper table:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-markdown" data-lang="markdown"><span class="line"><span class="cl">| (Index) | Value         |
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">|---------|---------------|
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">|       1 | &#39;2&#39;           |
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">|       2 | &#39;sample text&#39; |
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="consoletime">console.time()</h3>
<p>Starts a timer with a given label. Up to 10,000 simultaneous timers can be run
on a given page. It should be stopped with <code>console.timeEnd()</code> with the label as
parameter. to print the time in milliseconds. Timer&rsquo;s current time can be printed
without stopping by using <code>console.timeLog()</code>.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">time</span><span class="p">()</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">timeLog</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="c1">// After 2 seconds
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="c1"></span><span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">timeEnd</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="c1">// End after approximately 5 seconds
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><p>The result would be:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-console" data-lang="console"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">default: 2130.149034298985 ms
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">default: 5682.704833984375 ms
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="consoletrace">console.trace()</h3>
<p>Outputs a <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/console#stack_traces">stack trace</a>
to the function in which this method is called. Suitable to identify the source
of a function call.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="kd">function</span> <span class="nx">call_void</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">trace</span><span class="p">()</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="kd">function</span> <span class="nx">call_call_void</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="nx">call_void</span><span class="p">()</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nx">call_call_void</span><span class="p">()</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>The result would be:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-console" data-lang="console"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">console.trace
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">call_void
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="go">call_call_void
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><p>You can read more about these and also see some examples at:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/console#examples">MDN web docs</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/obj_console.asp">w3schools</a></li>
</ol>
]]></content:encoded></item></channel></rss>